         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ bot Garden ¶ 1/8/72. ¶  ¶ The same ship, dear Dr Hooker, which brings you this letter, brings nine Cycas stems from North Queensland, the first which ever reached Europe. I was long anxiou...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.08.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 48.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1/8/72.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The same ship, dear Dr Hooker, which brings you this letter, brings nine <name key="Cycas">Cycas</name> stems from North Queensland, the first which ever reached Europe. I was long anxious to try them, as stems 70 feet high can be obtained! But the intrusion on my Directorship and the loss of time merely to defend my Department brought this with other matters to the background. Please select the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">two</hi>
               </seg> best of these nine, one for Kew and one for Mr Booth of Flottback.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Flottbeck nursery, near Hamburg.</p>
               </note> If they <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">do</hi>
               </seg> arrive, and like Encephalartos <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">do</hi>
               </seg> thrive again then I will get you a stem as long as a double oxen team with two drays can bring it over the mountains. My efforts in this direction, carried out with great spirit and energy by Mr Fitzalan, have led to one astounding fact, namely that <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">millions</hi>
               </seg> of <name key="Cycas">Cycas</name>, (all tall) exist on a mountain chain not previously trodden, where Mr Fitzalan went to search. So there will be a new source of export, just like here in the south with the <name key="Todea">Todea</name>s.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will write fully by mail. Freight to London is paid.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Orchids for Mr Bentham will come by the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">steamer</hi>
               </seg> Sommersetshire;<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Somersetshire.</p>
               </note> therefore they may arrive as early as the <name key="Cycas">Cycas</name>.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The stems are consigned to the care of mess Ch Blackith &amp; Co Cox Quay. Lower Thames Str<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">London.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I believe this is the only gigantic <name key="Cycas">Cycas</name> in the world, and the only gregarious one.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">I believe ... gregarious one <seg style="font-style: italic; ">written in the central margin.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cycas">Cycas</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Encaphalartos">Encaphalartos</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Todea">Todea</name>
            </p>
         </div>
